# Azure Deployment — {{ project_name }}

## Resources Required

| Resource | Azure Service | Purpose |
|----------|--------------|---------|
| Backend API | Azure Container Apps | Hosts Spring Boot 4 application |
| Database | Azure Database for PostgreSQL (Flexible Server) | Data persistence |
| Container Registry | Azure Container Registry | Docker image storage |
| Secrets | Azure Key Vault | Stores OAuth secrets, JWT keys |
| AI Services | Azure AI Services | (Optional) AI/ML capabilities |

## Initial Setup

### 1. Create Resource Group

```bash
az group create --name {{ project_slug }}-rg --location eastus
```

### 2. Deploy Infrastructure

```bash
cd infra/azure
az deployment group create \
  --resource-group {{ project_slug }}-rg \
  --template-file main.bicep \
  --parameters projectName={{ project_slug }}
```

### 3. Configure Secrets in Key Vault

```bash
az keyvault secret set --vault-name {{ project_slug }}-kv --name jwt-secret --value "your-secret"
az keyvault secret set --vault-name {{ project_slug }}-kv --name google-client-id --value "your-id"
az keyvault secret set --vault-name {{ project_slug }}-kv --name google-client-secret --value "your-secret"
```

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions handles deployment automatically:
- **On push to `main`**: builds Docker image → pushes to ACR → deploys to Container Apps
- See `.github/workflows/backend.yml` for details

## Required GitHub Secrets

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `AZURE_CREDENTIALS` | Service principal JSON for Azure login |
| `AZURE_CONTAINER_REGISTRY` | ACR login server URL |
| `AZURE_CONTAINER_APP_NAME` | Container App resource name |
| `AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP` | Resource group name |
